# Local analytics Postgres -- compose-side overrides.
#
# `docker compose` reads `.env` from the same directory as `compose.yml`
# (not the orchestrator's root `.env`), so put compose-only variables
# here. Copy to `.env` before customizing:
#
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# All four variables are optional -- `compose.yml` substitutes the same
# defaults when an entry is unset. Override `POSTGRES_PASSWORD` (at
# minimum) before exposing the port off-host or storing real data.
#
# Note: `compose.yml` pins the host bind to 127.0.0.1, so this service
# is unreachable off-host regardless of any firewall configuration.
# Re-binding to 0.0.0.0 is intentionally a code change, not a config
# change, to avoid a permissive `.env` accidentally exposing the
# database.

# POSTGRES_DB=orchestrator_analytics
# POSTGRES_USER=orchestrator
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=orchestrator
# POSTGRES_PORT=5432
